body:
 I (26F) have a very rocky relationship with my father, to say the least. He has had at least 4 relationships with other women while he was still married to my mother, and due to a fallout we have not spoken in years. He is also very wealthy, and constantly likes to remember this fact.

&#x200B;

A year ago he tried getting in contact with me again, and I let him in. We are nearing Christmas, and he got me some presents. A pretty good cell phone, an educational board game (Cashflow), and an illuminated globe. I feel like two of these are the kind of gift you would get for a middle school student, and I have no use for the phone because I already have a very good one (he knows what model I own – I bought it a year ago by investing a decent amount of money even if it was on sale, but I know this phone would last me for years).  

&#x200B;

WIBTA if I told him I do not want any of these presents and that he can have them back, as I have no use for them or have no place for them in my house (the globe is particularly bulky)? I'm a frugal person and I usually buy only what is strictly necessary. I told him to ask me before buying anything because in most cases I would not need it.

