body:
I'm M25, she's F24 and we've been together for about a year now. I make about \~250k per year and she makes around 45k and at the start of our relationship she would tell her friends how much I make and it was annoying as they would be all up in my business and I just wanted her to respect my privacy. So she stopped, or so I thought she did. Friday night I went to her work party and when we sat down at our table her work friends were there and they're all like hey man heard you make 250k what do you do, what do you do with the money etc etc. This pissed me off and when we got home I confronted her about it and she said she let it slip on accident because all of the women in the office were talking about how much their SO's make and she just blurted mine out. I was still mad and have been being dry towards her for like a day and she said I'm being a total asshole about this and being a child.

AITA?

&#x200B;

text:
AITA For Getting Mad at my GF For Telling People How Much Money I Make? I'm M25, she's F24 and we've been together for about a year now. I make about \~250k per year and she makes around 45k and at the start of our relationship she would tell her friends how much I make and it was annoying as they would be all up in my business and I just wanted her to respect my privacy. So she stopped, or so I thought she did. Friday night I went to her work party and when we sat down at our table her work friends were there and they're all like hey man heard you make 250k what do you do, what do you do with the money etc etc. This pissed me off and when we got home I confronted her about it and she said she let it slip on accident because all of the women in the office were talking about how much their SO's make and she just blurted mine out. I was still mad and have been being dry towards her for like a day and she said I'm being a total asshole about this and being a child.

AITA?

&#x200B;

body:
So, something that's been going on in my life since I've left for college is that I've struggled a lot with gender dysphoria. I finally decided to transition last September, and I did it. I had previously came out to my family, mentioned to them I was transgender, and they were less than supportive. This time around, I did not tell them because I wanted to be able to go through it, see if anything changed and go from there.

&#x200B;

I ended up feeling so much happier, and I know this is right for me. Unfortunately, when it came time to tell my family that I was transgender, it went much worse than before. For better or for worse, only my mom has spoken to me since I came out in April. My sister did not reach out to me or speak to me, my father said nothing, and my mother claimed I was being selfish and that I didn't think of how my transition would effect them. 

&#x200B;

I tried to move on, put this in the past. Unfortunately, only my mother would speak to me. I've tried texting my younger sister, who is now a senior in high school, about every two weeks to try and get her to talk to me. I asked her how her prom went, about her vacation, about her auditions, etc. but she never replied. I sent her pictures of my vacation, and she ignored me. 

&#x200B;

So, I've been feeling very hurt and unsupported by family. I decided to call my mother, and I mentioned to her that my sister still will not text me back or anything, and that it was starting to upset me. My mother told me that It was very hard for my sister to go through this and that she needs time. She told me my sister is busy, applying for colleges, trying to work on her theater work, and she just can't handle me right now. I was told I'm not respecting that by continuing to text her, and that I should stop.

&#x200B;

This obviously upset me, and my mother told me that "you just have to accept that people don't know how to feel about this and we need time." I hung up on my mother, and was very upset. 

&#x200B;

I've thought a lot about this, and I'm thinking of cutting ties with them. I am going through a very hard time with my life, and feel like if they weren't here for me during some of my toughest times, why should I stick around for them? One of my friends says I shouldn't give up on them, and I should keep trying, but it is very hard to continue going through this each time we talk. WIBTA if I slowly cut them out forever?

&#x200B;

TLDR: Family says they need more time after three months of me coming out as trans, they have too much going on in their lives to be there for me or have any connection to me. Thinking of slowly cutting them out forever.

